Title: Series: The story of Abraham
Description: Abraham and Sarah entering Egypt (Genesis 12:1-13); Abraham rides a horse and wears a pointed hat; Sarah rides side-saddle on a donkey and wears a semi-transparent veil over her face; after Heemskerck Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Dirk Volkertsz Coornhert
Curator's comments: From a series of six plates (New Hollstein 8-13). A related drawing in the Muzeum Narodowe, Poznan.
Bibliographic references: New Hollstein (Dutch & Flemish) / The New Hollstein: Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts 1450-1700 (8) (Maarten van Heemskerck)
Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (10-13) (Coornhert)
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Capt Edward G Spencer-Churchill
